<HEAD>Gunmen Kill Policeman Outside U.S. Base</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three attackers shot and killed a
policeman near his house in front of his wife and two children near
the U.S.-run Clark Air Base, police reported Sunday.
   Police Capt. Marcelino Ibanez identified the victim as Patrolman
Jerico Gabiola. He said the attack occurred Saturday in Angeles
City, 50 miles north of Manila.
   The officer was opening the gate to his home when the gunmen
approached and one fired at close range with a 45-caliber pistol,
according to Ibanez.
   He said the killers escaped but a suspect was picked up Sunday
and was being questioned.
   There have been numerous killings in the vicinity of the Clark
Air Base and police blame communist rebels who have been fighting
the government for more than 19 years.
