<1ST_LINE>u a AM-PolicemanKilled 1stLd-Writethru a0679 07-24 0232</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Policeman Killed, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0679,0236</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lewiston Officer Is Shot At Car Accident Scene</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 6 grafs to UPDATE with murder charge and type of
gun used. Picks up 7th graf pvs `Payne, a...'</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LEWISTON, Maine (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A police officer was shot to death
Saturday when he responded to a car accident, authorities said.
   Officer David Payne, 26, was pronounced dead from a gunshot
wound after he was taken to Central Maine Medical Center in
Lewiston, said Police Chief Gregory Hanscom.
   Deputy Attorney General Fermand LaRochelle said Nicolo Leone, a
former Lewiston resident who lives in New York, was charged with
murder. Leone was in critical condition with gunshot wounds at the
medical center, a nursing supervisor said. A police guard was
posted at the hospital.
   Hanscom said Payne and two other officers responded to a report
of a car accident and that Payne, the first to arrive, approached a
man who ducked into the woods near the car.
   ``There was an exchange of gunfire,'' Hanscom said.
   A .44-caliber handgun was used in the killing, LaRochelle said.
   Payne, a father of two children ages 5 and 3, had been on the
police force two years.
   ``We grieve and feel terribly at the loss of this police
officer,'' Hanscom said.
   The last time a Lewiston policeman was killed in the line of
duty was 30 years ago this month.
</TEXT>
