<HEAD>China Reports Earthquake in Mongolia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake shook desolate Mongolia and
sent shocks across the border into China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region, the official Xinhua News Agency said Sunday.
   Chinese seismological stations said the quake occurred at 4:38
p.m. Saturday and measured 6.4 on the Richter scale, signifying a
tremor capable of causing severe damage in populated areas.
   Xinhua did not say if there were any reports of damage. It said
the quake was centered in far western Mongolia near where the
Soviet Union, Mongolia and China meet. It is a desolate and
sparsely inhabited region.
   The Richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on
seismographs.
