<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Killing     07-24 0127</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bangladesh-Killing,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Buddhist Rebels Kill 5 In Bangladesh</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Buddhist rebels shot and killed five
Moslem settlers and wounded three others in an ambush on a ferry in
southern Bangladesh, police said Sunday.
   The Chakma rebels are opposed to a government program resettling
Moslems from the plains to hilly land. They attacked a boat
Saturday ferrying 50 settlers near the hill town of Rangamati,
about 120 miles southeast of Dhaka, a police officer said.
   The Chakmas have been fighting a guerrilla war for more than a
decade to halt the program. They say the settlers would outnumber
them in the dense forests of the rugged Chittagong Hill Tracts,
which cover about 5,000 square miles. More than 4,000 people have
died in the conflict.
</TEXT>
