<HEAD>Cardinal's Return Delayed by Airplane Problems</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of Roman Catholics went to
Maputo's airport on Saturday and again Sunday to welcome home the
country's first cardinal, but he did not arrive.
   The news agency AIM said technical problems in the DC-10 of
Mozambique's national airline had forced a delay in the plane's
departure from Lisbon, Portugal, and Cardinal D. Alexandre Maria
dos Santos would not arrive until Monday.
   ``This morning hundreds of Catholics made their way to the
city's international airport, just as they had done on Saturday,
and with the same disappointing result,'' AIM reported. The plane
had been scheduled to arrive Saturday morning, but AIM said the
flight was postponed for ``technical reasons.'' It did not
elaborate.
   Dos Santos was to have presided at a Mass Sunday in the Maputo
Cathedral, his first since Pope John Paul II appointed him
cardinal, and various celebrations had been planned over the
weekend.
