<2ND_LINE>AM-NJ Bus Wreck, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0802,0339</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>35 Injured, 1 Seriously, As Bus En Route to Family Reunion Strikes
Bridge</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 6 grafs to UPDATE with driver being charged, fact
that he was not hurt, further details about accident. Picks up 6th
graf pvs, `Unlike a ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>EDISON, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A chartered bus carrying 46 people to a
family reunion Sunday slammed into a low overhead bridge that
peeled off its roof, toppling luggage onto passengers and injuring
35 people, police said.
   Most of the injured suffered cuts and wounds, said Edison Police
Sgt. Bill Bunting. They were taken to four hospitals.
   The only person admitted was Minnie McCrary, 44, of Norfolk,
Va., who was listed in critical condition with head injuries, said
Robert Loder, a spokesman for John F. Kennedy Hospital in Edison.
   The driver, Sherman Lassiter, 43, of Suffolk, Va., was charged
with careless driving, Bunting said. He said Lassiter, who works
for United Coach Corp. of Suffolk, was exceeding the speed limit
while traveling 35 to 40 mph and failed to observe a sign warning
of low bridge clearance.
   He said other accidents involving buses and trucks have occurred
at the underpass, most involving out of state drivers unfamiliar
with the low bridge and unattentive to a warning sign.
   The force of the collision sheared off most of the bus roof and
sent luggage from overhead racks toppling onto the passengers,
police said. The driver was unhurt, and the injured ranged in age
from 10 months to 60 years old, police said.
   Unlike a bus accident on the Garden State Parkway on Saturday,
in which 42 people were injured, there was no indication the driver
of the bus in Sunday's wreck was in possession of any drug
paraphernalia, Bunting said.
   The driver on Saturday, Annette Smalls, 29, of Newark, N.J., was
arrested after her Gray Lines tour bus, transporting a church group
from New York City to Atlantic City, went off the road and into
some trees, state police said.
</TEXT>
